190.name: Cinema City Novy Smichov
190.text: Cinema City Novy Smichov opened in the year 2001 and it is one of the most favourite cinemas in the whole of Czech Republic. It is located on the 3rd floor of the OC Novy Smichov shopping centre, one of the most visited shopping centres in the Czech Republic.

191.name: Cinema City Slovansky Dum
191.text: Cinema City Slovansky Dum is the only multiplex situated at the very heart of Prague city centre. Multiplex spans over a few floors of the unique Slovansky Dum. There are 2 bars for customers. Like the other multiplexes this one is also equipped with the most modern screening technology.

193.name: Cinema City Letnany
193.text: Cinema City Letnany was opened in October 2002. The multiplex, located in Shopping Centre Letnany, soon became a favourite hotspot for movie lovers. The multiplex consists of 8 fully air-conditioned motion-picture halls equipped with the best possible projection technology. One of the most distinct features of Cinema City Letnany is the largest hall with its panoramic screen, which gives the viewers a whole new experience of movie watching. Enhance your movie experience further by having a hot cup of coffee in our cinema café at the foyer.

228.name: CineStar Anděl
228.text: Multiplex CineStar Andel is one of eleven cinemas, that CineStar company operates in the Czech republic. Like the other multi-screen cinemas, this is equipped with the latest projection technology with a perfect sound. Regarding the size of the cinema this one is the greatest. It has fourteen halls with a total capacity for more than two thousand spectators.

3388.name: Cinema City Galaxie
3388.text: Galaxie belongs to the family of Cinema City. It is a traditional multiplex cinema, where visitors can choose from a wide range of movies. There are nine screening halls with large wide screens.

3390.name: Cinema City Zlicin
3390.text: Modern multiplex with high quality projection equipment is located in the Metropole Zlicin shopping gallery. Cinema is located on the 2nd mezzanine floor, in front of the large food court. Obviously like in all the modern cinemas, you can buy popcorn with ice-cold drinks and many kinds of sweets that will satisfy your tastes in the cinema foyer bar. You can also wait there before your movie starts settled comfortably in large leather sofas.

3392.name: Cinema City Flora
3392.text: Cinema City Flora is one of Prague's multiplex cinema, that offers a similar service like any other multiplex in Prague. Eight air-conditioned cinemas with perfect sound, endless supplies of popcorn and a wide range of films that is Cinema City Flora.

3394.name: IMAX
3394.text: IMAX Corporation is one of the world's leading entertainment technology companies, specializing in immersive motion picture technologies. The worldwide IMAX® theatre network is among the most important and successful theatrical distribution platforms for major event Hollywood films around the globe, with IMAX theatres delivering the world's best cinematic presentations using proprietary IMAX, IMAX® 3D, and IMAX DMR® technology.

3539.name: CineStar Cerny Most
3539.text: The CineStar is a network of multiplexes in the Czech Republic that was founded in 2001. With its twelve multiplexes it is one of the largest networks in the Czech Republic. Miltiplexes are equipped with the most modern screening technology and perfect sound Dolby Digital and Dolby Surround EX. CineStar Cerny Most is located at Cerny Most Shopping Centre. Parking is free for all the cinema visitors.

10920.name: Cinema City Olympia
10920.text: Cinema City Olympia, nowadays a traditional target for movie lovers, was opened in October 1999 as the first modern multiplex in the Czech Republic. It is situated in the Olympia shopping centre in the southern outskirts of the city of Brno.
